      <li>
        <p>
          Critique the following proof.
          If the proof adequately demonstrates why the statement is true,
          explain why.
          Otherwise, identify any errors and explain how to correct them.
          <theorem>
            <statement>
              <p>
                If <m>x</m> is a positive real number,
                then <m>x > 1</m> if and only if <m>1/x \lt 1</m>.
              </p>
            </statement>
          </theorem>
          <proof>
            <p>
              Suppose <m>1/x \lt 1</m>.
              Since <m>x</m> is positive,
              multiplying both sides of this inequality by <m>x</m> does not reverse the inequality and we obtain <m>1 \lt x</m>.
            </p>
          </proof>
